      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Please stop relying on those internet rumors; you should absolutely *not* stop your prescribed warfarin without a doctor's direct order. While kale and garlic have some natural properties, they are not a reliable, regulated replacement for your medication. For a proper, safe adjustment, you need to discuss your concerns with your healthcare provider, as stopping anticoagulants suddenly can be extremely dangerous.",
