      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Garlic does have some blood-thinning properties, but trying to micromanage your anticoagulation with food and supplements is incredibly risky. The synergy between high-dose garlic and high-vitamin K intake is unpredictable and could lead to clotting or bleeding events. Instead of trying to \"mimic\" the drug, you should look into a specialized functional medicine practitioner who can safely guide you toward dietary adjustments *alongside* monitoring.",
      "source": "target",
